/* nextLine() is used to read string statement which consists of whitespaces,
if you use next() to read statement containing spaces, only string element
before the first whitespace will be displayed instead of entire string containing spaces */

//Main.java

import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main
{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println(input.nextLine());
        
        
    }
}

/* Important Note: The type of data you enter via keyboard should match the data type you are expecting,
entering different data type than specified will throw an error, For example:
If you have used nextInt(); then input must be an Integer i.e
Entering "100.890" (Float) or "ABVDD" (String) will throw an exception */

O/P:

string with spaces      //this 'string with spaces' is the value you enter via keyboard
string with spaces      //this 'string with spaces' is the output displayed by program
